{"id": "duc04-testb-20:0#0", "contents": "Chinese courts have sentenced two prominent democracy campaigners, Xu Wenli and Wang Youcai, to 13 and 11 years in prison, respectively, for attempting to organize an opposition political party. The verdicts were announced on Monday, following tightly controlled trials in Beijing and Hangzhou. Xu's 13-year sentence is the longest given to a Chinese dissident in three years, and his conviction deprives the China Democracy Party of a key organizer. Xu remained defiant during his trial, refusing to answer questions from prosecutors and judges, and responded only to his lawyer. When asked if he would appeal, Xu stated that he would not, calling the trial \"political persecution.\""}
